sub_title: Ph.D. Student in Health Policy & Management
summary:
Atalay Demiray, MD, MSc
I am currently pursuing my Ph.D. in Health Policy and Management at Yale University. My area of interest lies in exploring the applications of artificial intelligence and machine learning in the field of medicine. I am also passionate about finding solutions to global health challenges to uphold public health. I hold a Master of Science degree in Health Economics, Policy, and Law from Erasmus University, wherein I was awarded the prestigious Jean Monnet Scholarship. My master's thesis focused on the "Regulation of Artificial Intelligence in Medicine: Upholding Public Health." Prior to this, I completed my Doctor of Medicine and Bachelor of Arts in International Relations from Koc University.
